According to the laws of Physics, a donut shaped planet could actually exist.
For the donut Earth to remain stable, it would've to rotate at very high speeds. Hence, days would last only few hours. The Gravity at the poles would become very strong- about twice as stronger than at the equator. The Moon would still continue orbiting Earth provided it is sufficiently far away. 

If the donut has zero tilt, inner edges would receive no sunlight while the outer edges would receive more sunlight, causing drastic temperature differences & extreme weathers. If tilt remains the same, both inner & outer edges would receive sufficient sunlight.
